author: Mike Chambers
title: DU hockey still ranked No. 1, Tanner Jaillet honored
text:
DU hockey still ranked No. 1, Tanner Jaillet honored Penn State surpasses Denver in U.S. College Hockey Online poll Share this: Joe Amon, The Denver Post University of Denver Goaltender Tanner Jaillet # 36 at Magness Arena. October 05, 2016 Denver, CO. By Mike Chambers | | The Denver Post January 16, 2017 at 6:53 pm Denver’s Martin Luther King Jr. Marade runs smoothly despite steady snow, cold 
The University of Denver on Monday retained the No. 1 ranking in the USA Today/USA Hockey Magazine poll, but slipped to No. 2 behind Penn State in the U.S. College Hockey Online poll. 
The Pioneers (15-5-4) split a two-game series at No. 12 Western Michigan last weekend while the Nittany Lions (16-2-1) swept unranked Michigan State at home. DU has the country’s second-toughest strength of schedule while Penn State’s is 34th. Related Articles January 7, 2017 Returning Troy Terry stays hot, scores two goals in Pioneers’ rout of Sun Devils 
Also Monday, Denver goalie Tanner Jaillet was named National Collegiate Hockey Conference goalie of the week after allowing only two goals in two games against Western Michigan. Although DU lost 3-0 on Friday before winning 7-2 Saturday, Western Michigan scored two empty-net goals in the opener and Jaillet was replaced late in the series finale with a 7-1 lead.
